external_knowledge:
- "active services" refers to subscriptions with a status of 'active';
- "top 10 customers" are those with the highest number of active subscriptions;
- "stars of a show" is a metaphor for the most prominent or important customers;
- "spotlight" is a metaphor for the services or subscriptions they have.

- "Multiple subscriptions" refers to customers who have more than one active subscription;
- "Total payments" is the sum of all payments made by the customer across their subscriptions;
- "Average payment amount" is the average amount of each payment made by the customer.

- "top patrons" refers to customers who have paid the most in total;
- "treasures they've bestowed upon us" refers to the total amount paid by each customer;
- "multitude of services they enjoy" refers to the number of services each customer is subscribed to;
- "last time they graced us with their payment" refers to the latest payment date for each customer.
